It is a [[Equivalence Relation]]

A Trace is a [[Word]] that is valid in an LTS

We first define a function trace, that returns all of the traces possible from a starting point

$$\text{trace}(x) = \{ w \in L^* | \exists x' | x \overset{w}{\twoheadrightarrow} x' \}$$

Trace set always contains $$\epsilon$$


Then $$x \equiv_T y <=> \text{trace}(x) = \text{trace}(y)$$

Breaks on paths that are not [[Deterministic]]

